2015-11-03 Tesla Motors Inc. has named former Google executive Jason Wheeler as its chief financial officer, replacing Deepak Ahuja, who announced in June that he planned to retire this year, CNBC reported.Wheeler is currently Google's vice president of finance. Ahuja has been at the company since 2008, seeing the company through its initial public offering,the Wall Street Journalreported.  BREAKING: Tesla has hired former Google exec. Jason Wheeler to be its new CFO, and has hired Jon McNeill as VP of Sales/Service. 	&mdash; CNBC Now (@CNBCnow) November 3, 2015  